{
  "stem": "1677.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 339.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And since the people who knew how to pray, prayed, people were singing the Kol Nidre, nobody stopped-- stopped us.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I did not know what they were doing, because I did not know any Kol Nidre.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I didn't know any Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And then came the famous story, which 100 people before me said and will say, that there was such a wonderful smell all over the camp.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they called us in at lunchtime.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "There was always such a gong.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they called us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we went.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And they roasted a pig, a huge, beautiful pig.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And they said come on, Jews, your big holiday today.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "You should see how humane we are to you.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And do you know, we were standing there, and that is the first time I was proud that I am Jewish.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And maybe the only time in my life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But that was the first time that nobody went forward, nobody in this empty stomach.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And it would have been, Hasidically and Halalically, absolutely permissible under such circumstances.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But-- and there I realized, slowly, in my imagination, what the tradition means, like the 'Tradition.' To me, it wasn't a religious thing.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "It was tradition.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "You don't eat on Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "You don't eat on Yom Kippur, finish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But it was somehow-- I felt there was more to it than just not eating.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Today, I know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And then, suddenly, the panic, transportations are commencing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And in the first transportation, 1st of October, 1944, we were put in, because they cleaned out the camp, cleaned out the camp.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From the-- from the 15th of September to the 30th of September, a fortnight.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I said to-- I went with this Pole, he was with me in the wagon.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
